Program: The Forum
Title: 12/05/2012 GMT
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00rc9dd
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 13 May 2012
Three variations on the theme of Second Chances: for the last thirty years, the acclaimed British photographer Nick Danziger has kept being drawn back to troubled places from Afghanistan to Bosnia, to meet people and document their lives. Fictional second chances in the latest novel by the Chinese-American author Gish Jen: do countries, as well as people, deserve another bite of the cherry? And joining us from California is Van Phillips, the American inventor whose revolutionary artificial leg design has given a new lease of life to both himself and countless other amputees world-wide. Illustration by Emily Kasriel: second chances - another shot at life. Show less